      "commit_id": null,
      "commit_url": null,
      "created_at": "2022-03-21T00:16:20Z",
      "updated_at": "2022-03-21T00:17:32Z",
      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "This seems to fix it...\r\n\r\nThe change of the nTimeOffset data type from int to int64_t in \r\n\r\n[https://github.com/RandyMcMillan/bitcoin/commit/65f78a111ff52c2212cc0a423662e7a41d1206dd#diff-86e079f53ae0a450c42ec1d282a458154002b99d5802b9c1f7396e209c67bdfaR176](https://github.com/RandyMcMillan/bitcoin/commit/65f78a111ff52c2212cc0a423662e7a41d1206dd#diff-86e079f53ae0a450c42ec1d282a458154002b99d5802b9c1f7396e209c67bdfaR176)\r\n\r\nseems to be the root of the issue...\r\n\r\nPatch/FIx:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\ndiff --git a/src/qt/guiutil.cpp b/src/qt/guiutil.cpp\r\nindex d6706fd009..877de36faf 100644\r\n--- a/src/qt/guiutil.cpp\r\n+++ b/src/qt/guiutil.cpp\r\n@@ -750,7 +750,7 @@ QString formatPingTime(std::chrono::microseconds ping_time)\r\n \r\n QString formatTimeOffset(int64_t nTimeOffset)\r\n {\r\n-  return QObject::tr(\"%1 s\").arg(QString::number((int)nTimeOffset, 10));\r\n+  return QObject::tr(\"%1 s\").arg(QString::number(nTimeOffset, 10));\r\n }\r\n \r\n QString formatNiceTimeOffset(qint64 secs)\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/compare/master...RandyMcMillan:1647799609-1647799494-master-18953\r\n\r\nThe argument used to be an int \r\n\r\nQString formatDurationStr(int secs); \r\n\r\nNOTE:\r\n\r\n[https://github.com/RandyMcMillan/bitcoin/commit/65f78a111ff52c2212cc0a423662e7a41d1206dd#diff-86e079f53ae0a450c42ec1d282a458154002b99d5802b9c1f7396e209c67bdfaR176](https://github.com/RandyMcMillan/bitcoin/commit/65f78a111ff52c2212cc0a423662e7a41d1206dd#diff-86e079f53ae0a450c42ec1d282a458154002b99d5802b9c1f7396e209c67bdfaR176)\r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### **A note on debugging/testing:**\r\n\r\n### **This issue may be illusive because it takes 5 peers connected - to be expressed.**\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/ae005a647ffa1d457c5c7a0528cb29f3b1937b96/src/timedata.cpp#L76\r\n\r\n\r\n### **Spoofing the node time is useful:**\r\n\r\nAs mentioned above +/- one day triggers a similar\r\ncondition.\r\n\r\nOne difference that I have noticed is that\r\nwhen the time is spoofed negative - all nodes that connect\r\nprior to the bug - don't begin syncing with the node - besides\r\nthe initial handshake.\r\n\r\n```shell\r\ndiff --git a/src/util/time.cpp b/src/util/time.cpp\r\nindex f7712f0dc8..6872a6871e 100644\r\n--- a/src/util/time.cpp\r\n+++ b/src/util/time.cpp\r\n@@ -30,7 +30,7 @@ int64_t GetTime()\r\n \r\n     time_t now = time(nullptr);\r\n     assert(now > 0);\r\n-    return now;\r\n+    return now - 24*60*60;\r\n }\r\n \r\n bool ChronoSanityCheck()\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nOn the contrary - when the time is spoofed in the\r\npositive - the first node will begin to sync (send block data).\r\n\r\n\r\n```shell\r\ndiff --git a/src/util/time.cpp b/src/util/time.cpp\r\nindex f7712f0dc8..6872a6871e 100644\r\n--- a/src/util/time.cpp\r\n+++ b/src/util/time.cpp\r\n@@ -30,7 +30,7 @@ int64_t GetTime()\r\n \r\n     time_t now = time(nullptr);\r\n     assert(now > 0);\r\n-    return now;\r\n+    return now + 24*60*60;\r\n }\r\n \r\n bool ChronoSanityCheck()\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nTweaking the -maxtimeadjustment setting seems to have an effect that I haven't fully\r\nlooked into... more testing with the patches above may offer some more insight...\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ make appbundle && ./Bitcoin-Qt.app/Contents/MacOS/Bitcoin-Qt -signet -maxtimeadjustment 10000000\r\n```\r\n",
